The paper deals with community detection in social networks, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The study also involves analyzing and comparing various algorithms, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The evaluation metrics used in the study, such as internal density, cut ratio, and conductance, are commonly used in the analysis of network structures, which falls under the category of social and economic networks (cs.SOC) and systems and control (cs.SD).
